# secIRC Cursor AI Configuration

## Project Overview
This is a secure IRC (Internet Relay Chat) implementation with both server and client components.

## Development Environment
- Python 3.8+ with virtual environment in `venv/`
- FastAPI for web API endpoints
- SQLAlchemy for database operations
- WebSocket support for real-time communication
- Comprehensive security features including encryption and authentication

## Code Style & Standards
- Use Black for code formatting
- Use Flake8 for linting
- Use MyPy for type checking
- Follow PEP 8 conventions
- Use type hints for all functions and methods
- Write comprehensive docstrings for all public functions

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── server/          # IRC server implementation
├── client/          # IRC client implementation
├── protocol/        # IRC protocol handling
├── security/        # Security and encryption modules
└── web/             # Web interface (if applicable)

config/              # Configuration files
tests/               # Test files
scripts/             # Setup and utility scripts
```

## Key Dependencies
- FastAPI: Web framework
- SQLAlchemy: Database ORM
- Cryptography: Encryption/decryption
- WebSockets: Real-time communication
- Pydantic: Data validation
- PyJWT: JWT token handling

## Development Workflow
1. Always activate virtual environment: `source venv/bin/activate`
2. Run tests before committing: `pytest`
3. Format code: `black src/ tests/`
4. Lint code: `flake8 src/ tests/`
5. Type check: `mypy src/`

## Security Considerations
- All user data must be encrypted
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Use secure defaults for all configurations
- Validate all input data
- Log security events appropriately

## Testing
- Write unit tests for all modules
- Use pytest for testing framework
- Aim for high test coverage
- Test both success and failure scenarios
- Include integration tests for critical paths

## Documentation
- Document all public APIs
- Include usage examples in docstrings
- Keep README files updated
- Document configuration options
- Provide clear error messages